The paper discusses the implementation of the MapReduce model on distributed-memory parallel machine models, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). It also involves analyzing the work and communication volume, which relates to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Performance (cs.PF). The paper also presents upper and lower bounds, which is a common topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
